How to write hard to test code?

- mixing new with logic
- looking for things
- work in constructor
- global state (singleton)
- static methods
- deep inheritance

The core of the problem is writing testable code!

Just write some code and send it to the test engineers...
At that point it is already too late!
The tester cannot write a good test.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

How to write testable code?

- good OO design
- dependency injection
- TDD